<br>
For example, if you listen to the songs &quot;Damage, Incorporated&quot; and &quot;Unforgiven&quot; back-to-back, you will hear two completely different bands.  In the Cliff Burton days, their songs were hard-core and made you want to kick someone's ass.  In the post-Cliff days, we get shit like &quot;So close no matter how far...couldn't be much more from the heart....forever trust in who we are....and nothing else matters&quot;  Someone PLEASE explain what the fuck that even means?  Did they just have a computer randomly generate some stupid-assed lyrics?<br>
<br>
Back in the old days, you never had to wonder what they were talking about.  &quot;Honesty is my only excuse...try to rob us of it, but it's no use...steamroller action crushes all....victim is your name and you shall fall!&quot;  Easy to follow and gets you pumped up.  Songs like Unforgiven and Nothing Else Matters make me want to recycle or plant a garden.<br>
<br>
As far as the topic goes, no I have not heard the new Metallica shit.  I was disappointed in And Justice For All, but really got pissed when the black album came out.  Once &quot;One&quot; became popular on MTV, Metallica became main stream and sold out.  The fuckers should have been forced to change their name. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noobtar>Noobtar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 295<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/16/03 6:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4222.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The New Kids on the Block of Metal</span><hr size=1> hahahahah<br>
