<br>
Losing Cliff was understandably a huge blow. The music will inevitably be different when someone of his caliber isnt contributing anymore. I'd even go as far as to say that maybe they wanted to tone it down some after that horrible bus accident. But everyone will have their own opinion on the matter.<br>
<br>
When Audioslave came out, I didn't want anything to do with it. I was (and still am) a big Rage fan. Their music, and especially the lyrics, brought me meaning when I needed it most. I knew the reincarnation would be nothing like the band I had grown to love. After I finally bought the album, I found that I was right; it was not the same, but still very good music in it's own respect. <br>
<br>
My point being, just because something is different, doesn't mean it's completely worthless. <br>
<br>
